cs.CR, cs.WEB, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.HC 

This paper investigates the usage of browser features on the modern web, including aspects related to security vulnerabilities. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Security and Privacy), cs.WEB (Web Technologies), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
